        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 3:53PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 353 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stapleton, or 6 miles north of Loxley, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Stapleton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
